cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use OpenWorld in your research, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "OpenWorld: A Zero-Dependency Framework for Verified Symbolic World Models"
abstract: >-
  OpenWorld builds, optimizes, and deploys verified symbolic world models —
  simulated environments whose dynamics are explicit, auditable Python code
  (optionally synthesized and verified by an LLM) rather than opaque neural
  weights. Worlds serialize to a portable JSON spec, render to a self-contained
  SVG model card, compose into worlds-within-worlds, and deploy as a stateless
  FastAPI inference server. The core is zero-dependency.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Schwoebel
    given-names: Jim
version: 0.3.0
date-released: "2026-07-01"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/quome-cloud/openworld"
url: "https://github.com/quome-cloud/openworld"
keywords:
